                    <comment id="12829786" author="martint" created="Thu, 4 Feb 2010 21:14:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Simple fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12829790" author="simonw" created="Thu, 4 Feb 2010 21:22:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Current implementation of ParallelMultiSearcher uses a cached thread pool with a core size of 0 and a keep alive time of 60 seconds. This will not leak any threads but closing it is a good idea anyway. I will move this to minor and I don&apos;t think its a bug either but good that you found it!&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12829851" author="thetaphi" created="Thu, 4 Feb 2010 23:29:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll commit this soon - Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12829866" author="thetaphi" created="Fri, 5 Feb 2010 00:06:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision: 906744&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks Martin!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12926254" author="rcmuir" created="Fri, 29 Oct 2010 13:59:10 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;reopening for possible 2.9.4/3.0.3 backport.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12926288" author="thetaphi" created="Fri, 29 Oct 2010 15:06:44 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;2.9 uses no executors, so only 3.0.3&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12926289" author="thetaphi" created="Fri, 29 Oct 2010 15:18:57 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This was already backported with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2494&quot; title=&quot;Modify ParallelMultiSearcher to use a CompletionService instead of slowly polling for results&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-2494&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
